  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No one was asking for a citizenship until an outside Jew and a woman [INAUDIBLE], yes, I want to go to America, needed to a citizenship or needed some papers.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the rules are very harsh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Rules are you've got to find your grandfather paid taxes for in 1867.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was born that domicile.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can read you about these rules, rules which a plain person it's impossible to-- And they give you six months.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That if in six months you still cannot proof your citizenship, you will be deported.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, during the six months, we can give you a postponement, provided that you have some paper or want to apply for some paper.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you go to the police station.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Police station had a sign, [NON-ENGLISH], not in your own town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And over there, they give you a postponement of six months, otherwise you'll be deported.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But Jews in the Dovhoje and other places to say we're deported, we knowing what it means.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who wants to deport?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where to?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What for?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who am I--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, the men are in the labor camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the children are, and the women are no income.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they take it very easy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at one point, the gendarmes interplay their laws and their own way to their discretion.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They take at random a Sunday morning, I was there in Dovhoje, and take some families, not with children because they know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And take them away to a place, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know, by bus they take them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And finally from [NON-ENGLISH], we hear they took them away to [NON-ENGLISH] and other places.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And over there, they put them over the border to Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was already occupied Soviet territory, and there are Ukrainians, and there are Germans there.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
